         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne ¶ bot Garden ¶ 20/5/72 ¶  ¶ I am always pleased to see your handwriting, dear Mr Bentham, and trust, that you are well. It is wonderful, how you maintain your bodily strength and mental powe...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">72.05.20a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To George Bentham</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew Correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1871-81, f. 40.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">bot Garden</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">20/5/72</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am always pleased to see your handwriting, dear Mr Bentham, and trust, that you are well. It is wonderful, how you maintain your bodily strength and mental power. May it long be so!</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your notes on <name key="Euphorbiaceae">Euphorbiaceae</name> are very interesting.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">G. Bentham to M, 10 March 1872.</p>
               </note> As far back as 1847 I gave the name Euph. chamaesycoides to what Sonder in the Linnaea subsequently identified as the right E. chamaesyce.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Sonder (1856c), p. 562, does not mention M's presumed ms. or herbarium name. </p>
               </note> The final clearing up of these Euphorbiaceous plants will be important. A few novelties occur in the parcels of <name key="Euphorbiaceae">Euphorbiaceae</name>, sent by the Northumberland-Steamer in March.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I will send you soon the <name key="Orchideae">Orchideae</name>, but think that it will be best to exclude other Monocotyledonous orders from the volume. </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>To the new volume of the "genera"<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Bentham &amp; Hooker (1862-83).</p>
               </note> I look forward with intense interest.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Always your regardful</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">The bound copy of vol VII fragm. must have reached Kew and yourself 2 month ago.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B64.11.02. See G. Bentham to M, 10 March 1872 and G. Bentham to M, 17 April 1872.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Yours F.v.M.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>What I have sent as a <name key="Streblus">Streblus</name> is called by Kurz <name key="Gironniera%20ilicifolia">Gironniera ilicifolia</name>.<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Kurz treated <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Gironniera</seg> as a subgenus of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Sponia</seg>, and described <seg style="font-style: italic; ">S. ilicifolia </seg>in Kurz (1872), p. 448. Bentham (1863-78), vol. 6, p. 181 treated M's <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Streblus">Streblus</name>
                     </seg> as a <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Pseudomorus</seg>.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
